<br>
1. Maintain terrain advantage. According to your situation, your opponents are situated at an elevated location. This gives them an elevated position advantage (meaning they can look down and see you easily while you can't look up and see them easily). The terrains in SWG are designed to emulate real life physics, meaning you will run up a slope slower than you run down. Unless you have really good scouting/ranger skills you will definitely walk up an elevated terrain slower giving your opponent the chance to kill you before you get to them. <br>
<br>
2. Since they are the invaders. Use your home court advantage. Do not go to your enemies, let them come to you. For short, fight in your own terms. Use your housing and other structures as cover. Create a situation where the enemy has to come to you and fight in your terms. If they are invading your city that means they are looking for a fight, they WILL come to you. If you mindlessly charge your enemy it'll be just like painting a huge target crosshair on top of your head. Again, use cover, your enemy can't shoot thru walls.<br>
<br>
3. If the invaders overwhelm your forces 2 to 1 then use guerilla tactics. Urban warfare is the most dangerous and bloody kind of warfare. It is used when a force is at a disadvantage in terms of man power and fire power. It is used to whittle down invading forces. Again use your housing/structures as cover, use your snipers (riflemen) to pick off your enemies one by one.  If they really want to get you, make them work for it and create a situation where they will suffer losses. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000028><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub60.ezboard.com/bcreaturehandlersofswg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zumbukfleshcarver>Zumbuk Fleshcarver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#70DB93>(11/20/03 2:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub60.ezboard.com/fcreaturehandlersofswgfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=140.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pets in PVP?</span><hr size=1> Alot of that advice would be great if terrain meant something in this game. But when you can shoot a laser through 40 feet of solid rock and hit your opponent, using terrain and things like that kinda falls through.<br>
<br>
One thing you can do if you are burning is run for water. Of course you cant do this on Tatooine unelss youre near an oasis. But other planets that have plentiful water sources can provide relief from a burn.<br>
<br>
Theres not alot you can do for a pet other than store it if it is on fire. Their resistance to heat may help prevent initial damage, but the fire DoT bypasses that each time it tics. I would suggest that if you ever get Master CH, to use something like a Rancor or Gurreck for PvP due to its higher HAM and damage, it might just make a difference in how long the pet stays alive. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.netset.com/~blazer/sig3.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
